57 PROPOSED AMENDMENT
58 (a) Each local board of education shall adopt a policy
59 requiring each public K-12 school under its jurisdiction to
60 broadcast The Star-Spangled Banner during school hours, at
61 least once per week.
62 (b)(1) A local board of education shall select for
63 broadcast, pursuant to subsection (a), any recording of the
64 first stanza of The Star-Spangled Banner that is archived
65 within the Library of Congress and available on the Library of
66 Congress website.
67 (2) A local board of education, alternatively, may
68 adopt a policy allowing, during school hours, for the
69 performance of the first stanza of The Star-Spangled Banner
70 from original sheet music, archived within the Library of
71 Congress and available on its website, by a school-sanctioned
72 band program, choral program, vocal group, or vocalist.
73 Upon ratification of this constitutional amendment, the
74 Code Commissioner shall number and place this amendment as
75 appropriate in the constitution omitting this instructional
76 paragraph and may make the following nonsubstantive revisions:
77 change capitalization, hierarchy, spelling, and punctuation
78 for purposes of style and uniformity; correct manifest
79 grammatical, clerical, and typographical errors; revise
80 internal or external citations and cross-references; harmonize
81 language; and translate effective dates.
